posts.title: Just a Reminder
posts.content:
I would like to remind everyone and Inform those who do not know.

The United States of America Created COVID-19 with tax payer money. This occurred through funding channeled by the National Institutes of Health (NIH) to EcoHealth Alliance, an organization led by Peter Daszak. Daszak spearheaded efforts at the Wuhan Institute of Virology in Wuhan, China, where this research originated. U.S. taxpayers, through federal funding, inadvertently financed the Gain-of-Function (GoF) experiments that ultimately led to the creation of COVID-19. This is an established fact.

EcoHealth Alliance's research endeavors related to bat coronaviruses and emerging infectious diseases were primarily funded by the NIH, USAID, and the Department of Defense. Just like the Ukrainian Biolabs that lead to the Monkey Pox outbreak. (See my previous posts to learn more about that.).

What Led to This?

In 2014, under the Obama Administration, growing political and lobbying pressure resulted in a temporary halt on GoF research. This moratorium was implemented due to significant concerns about the inherent risks of manipulating pathogens to make them more transmissible or dangerous.

https://www.nature.com/articles/514411a

By 2017, during the Trump Administration’s early months, administrative disarray following the resignation of the Health Secretary amid a corruption scandal created an opportunity for policy changes. In this chaotic transition, Dr. Anthony Fauci reinstated the funding of Gain-of-Function research, allowing these projects to resume without broader public awareness. Additionally, Fauci directed substantial non-competitive grants to Moderna for vaccine development, with allocations amounting to hundreds of millions of dollars—though the precise figures remain debated.

https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/29/us/politics/tom-price-trump-hhs.html

https://www.nih.gov/about-nih/who-we-are/nih-director/statements/nih-lifts-funding-pause-gain-function-research

Fauci utilized NIH mechanisms to fund EcoHealth Alliance under Peter Daszak. These funds facilitated GoF research at the Wuhan Institute of Virology until the containment of these experiments failed. Whether the release of the virus was accidental or intentional remains unclear. However, the timing—before a major U.S. election—raises suspicions, especially given its role in enabling mail-in voting and legal changes in key swing states. Some of these changes were later ruled unconstitutional.

Supporting Evidence:

https://reporter.nih.gov/project-details/9819304

https://www.technologyreview.com/2021/06/29/1027290/gain-of-function-risky-bat-virus-engineering-links-america-to-wuhan

https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/interactive/2021/a-science-in-the-shadows/

DARPA’s Potential Role and Project DEFUSE

The Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) becomes a critical component in this narrative. Project DEFUSE, proposed by EcoHealth Alliance, sought to manipulate coronaviruses under the guise of pandemic prevention but was initially declined by DARPA due to concerns about its risks. However, subsequent funding for similar research projects occurred, coinciding with the global emergence of COVID-19. DARPA’s involvement, even indirectly, deserves deeper scrutiny, as it could have played a pivotal role in enabling the circumstances that led to the pandemic.

Further Information:

https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/21066966-defuse-proposal

This narrative outlines a sequence of events involving the funding, execution, and concealment of high-risk research activities by the U.S. Government, spearheaded by Dr. Anthony Fauci, and rooted in groundwork laid during the Obama Administration. Here's a breakdown of the events and their implications:

Summary of Events:

  1. Initiation of Gain-of-Function Research:

https://x.com/IceMaster_T/status/1833861672538423459?t=jqXt_WmmRwNpgAY3iih7-w&s=19

Dr. Fauci played a central role in initiating Gain-of-Function (GoF) research, a controversial approach aimed at enhancing the transmissibility or pathogenicity of viruses. While this research was temporarily paused during the Obama Administration due to safety concerns, policies were carefully designed to leave room for future resumption.

  1. Policy Shift Under Trump:

Amid the administrative turbulence during the Trump Administration, including the resignation of the Health Secretary, Dr. Fauci discreetly reversed the GoF research moratorium. This policy change enabled funding to flow to EcoHealth Alliance, led by Peter Daszak, for research conducted at the Wuhan Institute of Virology.

  1. DARPA’s Role and Project DEFUSE:

The Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) allegedly became involved, funding Project DEFUSE. This initiative, led by Daszak, aimed to study bat coronaviruses and included plans to release infected bats back into the wild to assess spillover risks. The timeline for this activity coincides suspiciously with the outbreak of COVID-19.

  1. The Pandemic and Vaccine Rollout:

The virus, which caused symptoms resembling a severe cold for many, triggered a global pandemic. This paved the way for the rapid deployment of pre-developed vaccines, mandated for widespread use, under the guise of an emergency response. Vaccine hesitancy was met with campaigns labeling unvaccinated individuals as societal threats, further polarizing the public.

  1. Societal Consequences:

The pandemic response included:

Widespread censorship of dissenting views.

Economic disruptions such as inflation, business closures, and supply chain issues.

Mandates and restrictions on personal freedoms.

Media narratives perpetuating fear and division under the "Pandemic of the Unvaccinated" banner.

Implications:

This chain of events is characterized by strategic opportunism and systemic failures, culminating in significant public mistrust. The individuals and entities that benefited the most include pharmaceutical companies, media outlets, and policymakers who leveraged the crisis for economic or political gain.

Supporting Evidence:

https://x.com/IceMaster_T/status/1833861672538423459?t=AaF00jh0m7nx1lilzaB3TQ&s=19

https://x.com/R_H_Ebright/status/1450947395508858880?t=w3jXmCvxZY26gajxedknXA&s=19

https://video.wixstatic.com/video/1c4075_7caeb4d6d0bd4e4195cfd67161ba93d4/1080p/mp4/file.mp4

Conclusion:

Understanding and accepting the events leading up to the pandemic requires recognizing the roles of key individuals and institutions. The alleged manipulation of public perception and the disproportionate societal impact highlight the need for accountability. Identifying those who orchestrated and benefited from these events is critical for preventing similar occurrences in the future.
